The burial arrangement of deceased Nollywood actor, Karibi Fubara has been announced by the family.  Fubara’s funeral service will hold on Friday, February 11, 2022. This was made known in a statement shared on Instagram on Friday. According to the post, there will be a night of tributes on Tuesday February 8 at The Leisure Park in Lekki Phase one, Lagos State. funeral The service of songs will hold on February 6 at the House On The Rock Cathedral in Lagos. Karibi was announced dead on Wednesday, December 15, 2021. The God Calling actor had been diagnosed with cancer in 2020. The actor married celebrity stylist Yolanda Okere in December 2019. Karibi died at age 46.  Source ABUJA - Funeral arrangements have been announced for the late Mrs. Gbemisola Comfort Foyeke Soneye, the mother of the publisher of Per Second News, Mr. Femi Soneye. Mrs. Soneye, according to a statement on Wednesday, “died peacefully and entered Heaven’s gates” at St. Nicholas Hospital on December 1, 2015 after… In "Metro" By Mohammed Lawal   Zaria   -     A former Supreme Court Judge, Justice Saifullahi Muntaqa Coommassie has died at the age of 71 on Thursday evening after a brief illness. Alhaji Yusuf Saifullahi, son to the deceased, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Zaria that his… In "News" There was a face-off between Governor, Nyesom Wike of Rivers State and his predecessor, Rotimi Amaechi, on Saturday at the burial of a former Justice of the Supreme Court, Adolphus Karibi-Whyte, in the Abonnema, Akuku-Toru Local Government Area of the state. Amaechi, who is the Minister of Transportation, while speaking… In "Politics"